node_modules/
.DS_Store

# Self-render (`node installer/cli.mjs render`): the .claude/ output and the lock are
# COMMITTED, like a consuming project — the CI-dispatched hygiene harness reads the
# committed skills, and the waffle-doctor drift gate needs render + lock in git to be
# meaningful. Re-render AND commit after editing stacks/**. Worktrees are throwaway
# working state; .codex/ and .agents/ are non-targets here (targets: [claude]).
.claude/worktrees/
.codex/
.agents/
# waffle-label-hook.yml stays untracked — committing it would arm a live label→harness
# dispatch on this repo, which is not wanted here. Committed workflows: doctor (drift gate,
# required check on main), release-hook (#39), and post-merge-hook. The three paid
# Claude-dispatch hooks (hygiene, pr-green, pr-response) are EJECTED, not gitignored —
# `render` no longer pours them (see .waffle/waffle.yaml `eject:`), so there is nothing to
# ignore. doctor runs with --allow-missing so this deliberately-absent label render doesn't
# fail CI.
.github/workflows/waffle-label-hook.yml
.waffle/waffle.local.yaml
# …and the local lock it implies (#317): when a contributor's overlay actually feeds their render,
# `render` records THEIR hashes here, leaving .waffle/waffle.lock.json canonical (committed inputs
# only) and therefore identical for everyone. Machine-specific, exactly like the overlay — never
# commit it. Absent entirely on a machine with no overlay.
.waffle/waffle.local.lock.json
# Generated .waffle/ overview docs (cheat sheet + team intro, Markdown + branded HTML).
# Consumers commit these; here they are generated-only, covered by doctor's
# --allow-missing like the label-hook workflow above.
.waffle/CHEATSHEET.md
.waffle/TEAM.md
.waffle/cheatsheet.html
.waffle/team.html
# …and the per-agent avatar files + their Gravatar registration manifest (#157).
.waffle/AVATARS.md
.waffle/avatars/

# Obsidian
.obsidian/
